title: For Sale:  SKS, Type 56, Chinese, 7.62X39, all matching numbers, with bayonet $375
postcontent:
SKS, Type 56, Chinese, 7.62X39, all matching numbers, with bayonet $375. 

This rifle has been thoroughly cleaned and lubricated. All signs of cosmoline have been removed and all parts tested. This rifle is the real thing. It is not one of those shiney new rifles that has never saw any action.  This rifle is battle tested and ready to go.  If it could only talk, the history would be amazing. This semi-automatic rifle has been arguably considered one of the fathers of all modern semi-automatic rifles. It was one of the first weapons chambered for the 7.62x39mm M43 round, which was also used later in the AK-47.   It was used extensively by the Russian army during WWII. The SKS has a conventional carbine layout, with a wooden stock and no pistol grip. The SKS is a gas-operated weapon that has a spring-loaded operating rod and a gas piston rod that work the action via gas pressure pushing against them. Also, it has a "tilting bolt" action locking system.  The SKS's ten-round box magazine is fed from a stripper clip and rounds stored in the magazine can be removed by depressing a magazine catch located forward of the trigger guard (thus opening the "floor" of the magazine and allowing the rounds to fall out). In typical military use the stripper clips are disposable. If necessary they can be reloaded multiple times and reused. the barrel is chrome-lined for increased wear and heat tolerance from sustained fire and to resist corrosion from chlorate-primed corrosive ammunition, as well as to facilitate cleaning.  The front sight has a hooded post. "The rear sight is an open notch type which is adjustable for elevation from 100 meters to 1000 meters (110–1100 yards). There is also an all purpose "battle" setting on the sight ladder (marked "П"), set for 300 meters (330 yards). This is attained by moving the elevation slide to the rear of the ladder as far as it will go."  All military SKSs have a bayonet attached to the underside of the barrel, which is extended and retracted via a spring-loaded hinge.  The SKS is easily field stripped and reassembled without any tools other than an unfired cartridge.  The rifle comes with a cleaning rod running under the barrel, in the same style as the AK-47. 


There are some scuffs, dings, and scratches in the wood, but that is the history of this remarkable weapon! All parts match and fit nicely together. The action is very smooth. Here is your chance to own a piece of history and relive the life of the soldiers who have trusted their life to this historical weapon.  Own a piece of history today! $375
